    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a homeless employer scheme to help homeless people into work",
        "additional_details": "This scheme should include a guaranteed offer of an interview if they meet minimum criteria and targets.\r\n \r\nThis would help give the homeless a fighting chance and could: \r\n - help reduce homeless rates & antisocial behaviour;\r\n- help people who have become homeless with their wellbeing\r\n- help reduce squatters\r\n- enable them the opportunity to get off the streets\r\n- help them be a part of society and save the government money, by them contributing\r\n- improve the look and cleanliness of towns\r\n- reduce substance misuse and dependency\r\n- show them that they are a valued member of the community.",
        "background": "The Government should create and fund a scheme, like the disability confident employer scheme, to encourage more employers to recruit homeless people, to help them get back on their feet. ",
